    <div xml:id="PN336">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>vēṭṭa vēntaṉum veñciṉat tiṉaṉē</l>
<l>kaṭavaṉa kaḻippiva ṭantaiyuñ ceyyā</l>
<l>ṉoḷiṟumukat tēntiya vīṅkutoṭi maruppiṟ</l>
<l>kaḷiṟuṅ kaṭimarañ cērā cērnta</l>
<l>voḷiṟuvēṉ maṟavarum vāymūḻt taṉarē</l>
<l>yiyavaru maṟiyāp palliyaṅ kaṟaṅka</l>
<l>vaṉṉō</l>
<l>perumpē tuṟṟaṉṟiv varuṅkaṭi mūtū</l>
<l>raṟaṉilaṇ maṉṟa tāṉē viṟaṉmalai</l>
<l>vēṅkai veṟpiṉ virinta kōṅkiṉ</l>
<l>mukaivaṉap pēntiya muṟṟā viḷamulait</l>
<l>takaivaḷart teṭutta nakaiyoṭu</l>
<l>pakaivaḷart tiruntavip paṇpi ṟāyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The king who wants [her] is full of hot anger, (1)</l>
<l>her father does not discharge [his] duties, (2)</l>
<l>the elephant bulls with swelling ringed tusks that go up in [their]</l>
<l>resplendent faces do not join the protective trees, and the assembled (3f.)</l>
<l>bold warriors with resplendent spears keep [their] mouths shut. (5)</l>
<l>While many instruments sound that are not known even to the musicians, (6)</l>
<l>alas, (7)</l>
<l>big folly underwent this well-protected old town. (8)</l>
<l>She is without virtue indeed, (9a-c)</l>
<l>‒ the mother without [good] qualities (13cd)</l>
<l>who, by with a smile nurturing [and] raising as was fit (12)</l>
<l>[her] with eminent young breasts not [yet] fully grown of the beauty (11)</l>
<l>of the buds of cameg that unfold on the mountain of kino trees (10)</l>
<l>  in the victorious mountains, (9d)</l>
<l>  sat [there] growing enmity. (13ab)  </l>
</lg>
